<item>
            <title>[HADOOP-11143] NetUtils.wrapException loses inner stack trace on BindException</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HADOOP-11143</link>
                <project id="12310240" key="HADOOP">Hadoop Common</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;NetUtils.wrapException&lt;/tt&gt; is designed to aid debugging by including exception diagnostics in the wrapped &amp;amp; relayed exception.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;When a BindException is caught, we build the new exception  but don&apos;t include the original as the inner cause.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;this means it doesn&apos;t get logged, and while the host:port problem may be identifiable, the bit of the code playing up is now harder to track down.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;machine that doesn&apos;t bind&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
